description:
&lt;p&gt;The OT Service at Western Sussex Hospitals NHS Trust based at St.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard&#39;s Hospital Chichester are currently seeking a full or part&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;time job share B6 Occupational Therapist to work in our General&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medical Team, to  include weekend cover as required. This is a 12&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;month short term contract or could be a secondment for an internal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;candidate.  If you would like the opportunity to work flexibly in this busy and stimulating&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;environment, this would be the perfect job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the OT Department you will work alongside  B7, B6, B5, B4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and OT support staff to complete timely assessments and interventions,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; demonstrating sound clinical reasoning, a high level of autonomy and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the ability to make decisions around the safest and most appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;discharge destination.  You will also work collaboratively with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doctors, Nurses to help identify those who need further medical&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;assessment and intervention, and link in with Community Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;regarding ongoing assessment and care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gen Med team shares close links with  other inpatient teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; including A&amp;E, Neurology and Orthopaedics. We  cover a variety of&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;medical and elderly wards and conditions, including cardiology,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;respiratory, gastroenterology, vascular, frailty, dementia and falls,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; and our staff are  instrumental in palliative care to support people&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;being fast tracked home. We also staff the Emergency floor which is a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; rapid turnaround ward to avoid unnecessary admission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of in-patient general medical wards is essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and experience of admission avoidance is highly desirable, but you &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; will be provided with support and opportunities to develop your&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;knowledge and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with OT support staff and you will be responsible for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;their daily work and will gain experience of supervising other staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Good team support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* A supportive and reflective learning environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Regular professional formal and informal supervision with an annual&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; personal development review.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Opportunities to develop a wide range of core and specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; clinical skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Opportunity to engage in service wide clinical governance activities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Commitment to practice placements with strong links to University of&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Brighton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Katharine Carlisle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Occupational Therapy Operations Manager Western Sussex Hospitals NHS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Foundation Trust Direct Dial: 01243 831521 St. Richard’s Hospital:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01243 788122 ext 35199&lt;/p&gt;
